  "text": "ACCase gene resistance mutations in hexaploid wild oat Q Yu et al ACCase complementary DNA (cDNA) fragment cloning and sequencing Total RNA was extracted from leaf tissue of individual plants possessing all three ACCase mutations (1781 þ 2078 þ 2088) using the Plant RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany). gDNA contamination was removed using the TURBO-DNA free kit (Ambion, Austin, TX, USA), which is highly effective in removing trace quantities of DNA contamination. Oligo(dT)-primed first-strand cDNA was prepared from 2 mg total RNA using the Omniscript Reverse Transcription system (Qiagen). The primers NsiI1781F (modified from [CITATION_1] and SQCT-a1R were paired to amplify a 1122 bp cDNA fragment containing all known resistanceendowing ACCase gene mutation sites (1781, 1999, 2027, 2041, 2078, 2088 and 2096) , as well as polymorphic sites for the three ACCase gene copies in A. fatua [CITATION_2] . This fragment was cloned into the pGEM-T vector (Promega) and transformed into E. coli. White colonies with putative inserts were used as templates for PCR re-amplification of the 1122 bp fragment and screened for the 1781, 2078 or 2088 mutations using PCR-based markers (see below). Fragments that contained putative 1781, 2078 or 2088 mutations were selected for confirmatory sequencing using two forward primers, SQCT-a1F and NsiI1781F (Table 1) , with overlapping amplification regions.",
